<pre class='fragment'>
&lt;<span class="node">mod-tls</span>>
   <span class="comment">&lt;!--  -*- nxml -*-  --></span>
   <span class="comment">&lt;!--  place one certificate select for each serverName to match.  Use
       serverName="*" to provide the same certificate for all serverNames
       requested. 

       The close-on-failure="yes" attribute allows to control if the
       module should close the connection after a TLS handshake
       failure or leave the connection as is. Leave this setting as is
       to have a recommended secure configuration.
   --></span>
   &lt;<span class="node">certificate-select</span> close-on-failure=<span class="attrvalue">"yes"</span> 
                       key=<span class="attrvalue">"private.key"</span> 
                       cert=<span class="attrvalue">"certificate.crt"</span> 
                       serverName=<span class="attrvalue">"tls.example.com"</span> />
&lt;/<span class="node">mod-tls</span>>
</pre>
